==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philippize
<hw>Phil"ip*pize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Philippized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Philippizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to be on
Philip's side.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To support or advocate the cause
of Philip of Macedon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[See <er>Philippic</er>.]</ety> <def>To write or
speak in the style of a philippic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philister</ent>⟦br⟧
